It receives input in the abdominal neuromere and sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the abdominal neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).

value.value: Adult intrinsic neuron with bilateral VNC arbors (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a primary neuron (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It exits the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the abdominal neuromere and intermediate tectulum and sends output to the abdominal neuromere and intermediate tectulum (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is gaba (Eckstein et al., 2024). There is approximately one of these cells per organism with its soma in the prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
